caption: Table 1: Summary of Notation
description: This table summarizes the notations used throughout the paper.  It defines the key mathematical objects such as the set of features (X), labels (Y), noisy observations (Ÿ), hypothesis class (H), noisy kernel (K), and probability distributions (D(Ý)).  It clarifies the meanings of symbols used for sets, sizes, and operations relevant to the online classification framework.
